ABUJA – Foremost constitutional lawyer and human rights activist, Chief Mike Ozekhome, SAN, on Monday, stated the reason why he took over headship of defence team of the detained leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, Nnamdi Kanu.This is as he appeared before the Federal High Court, Abuja to lead Kanu’s defence team. According to Vanguard, Ozekhome, said his decision to take over Kanu’s defence, was based on the fact that he is facing an incompetent charge. “Right to self-determination is inalienable. It is guaranteed under both the Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria and the African Charter on Peoples’ Rights. I am here today because I believe that the charge against the Defendant is baseless”, he added. The Federal Government amended the charges against Kanu barely 24 hours to the commencement of his trial today. •Chief Mike Ozekhome, SAN ABUJA - Constitutional lawyer and human rights activist, Chief Mike Ozekhome, SAN, has been drafted into the legal team of Mazi Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB).This is as the case comes up today, Tuesday at the Federal High Court, Abuja amid… In "Top Stories" By Teddy Nwanunobi Abuja (Sundiata Post) — Leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu, was, on Tuesday, granted bail on health reasons in an Abuja Federal High Court 4 presided over by Justice Binta Nyako. Nyako, however, denied bail to three other pro-Biafra agitators, Chidiebere Onwudiwe, Benjamin Madubugwu… In "Top Stories" Abuja - A prominent lawyer, Mike Ozekhome (SAN), has said the United States must make a formal request for the extradition of Deputy Commissioner of Police, DCP Abba Kyari. Kyari was indicted by the Federal Bureau of Investigation in the fraud case against Ramon Abbas aka Hushpuppi in the US.… In "Top Stories"